MySQL Workbench is a cross-platform, visual database design tool developed
by MySQL.  It is the highly anticipated successor application of the
DBDesigner4 project.  MySQL Workbench is available as a native GUI tool
on Windows, Linux and OS X in different editions.

MySQL Workbench provides DBAs and developers an integrated tools
environment for:

* Database Design & Modeling
* SQL Development (replacing MySQL Query Browser)
* Database Administration (replacing MySQL Administrator)

The Community (OSS) Edition is available under the GPL.

Note:
You need to allow MySQL to accept incoming connection from outside
Open /etc/rc.d/rc.mysqld, you have to comment this line
SKIP="--skip-networking"
and restart MySQL Daemon
/etc/rc.d/rc.mysqld stop
/etc/rc.d/rc.mysqld start

Requirements: 
- lua (available on Slackware)
- wxGTK-2.8.12/wxPython-2.8.12 (available on SBo)
- sqlite3 (available on Slackware)
- ORBit2-2.14.19 (available on Slackware)
- GConf-2.32.1 (available on Slackware)
- libsigc++-2.2.10
- glibmm-2.32.0
- atkmm-2.22.6
- cairomm-1.10.0
- pangomm-2.28.4
- gtkmm-2.24.2
- ctemplate-2.2
- paramiko-1.7.7.1 (available on SBo)
  - pycrypto-2.5